Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Here's what's coming to Netflix in November Kelly Jensen, 9 News 7:32 p.m. EDT October 21, 2015 The Netflix company logo is seen at Netflix headquarters in Los Gatos, CA on Wednesday, April 13, 2011. Netflix has announced which movies, documentaries, and original programming will come to the streaming service beginning in November. 
While the list of movies may not impress at first, there are several highly-anticipated originals in the lineup, including new comedy from Aziz Ansari and new kids programming. 
We've embedded the complete list with descriptions at the end of our article. 
DOCUMENTARY: Idris Elba: Mandela, My Dad and Me (2015) Last Days in Vietnam (2014) Smithsonian Channel: The Day Kennedy Died (2013) Twinsters (2015) Do I Sound Gay? (2014) Amapola (2014) Best of Enemies (2015) - NOV 28 Electric Boogaloo: The Wild, Untold Story of Cannon Films (2014) - NOV 29 
NETFLIX ORIGINAL SERIES: even Deadly Sins: Season 1 Care Bears & Cousins: Season 1 - NOV 6 Master of None: Season 1 - NOV 6 John Mulaney: The Comeback Kid (2015) - NOV 13 With Bob and David: Season 1 - NOV 13 River (2015) - NOV 18 Marvel's Jessica Jones: Season 1 - NOV 20 
KIDS: The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie (2004) Julius Jr.: Season 2 Thomas & Friends: The Christmas Engines (2014) LeapFrog Letter Factory: Great Shape Mystery (2015) Atención Atención: Season 1 LEGO Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu: Season 3 - NOV 20 
AVAILABLE NOVEMBER 1: Girlfriends' Guide to Divorce: Season 1 Pasion de Gavilanes (2003) The Last Time You Had Fun (2014) Worst Year of My Life, Again: Season 1 
AVAILABLE NOVEMBER 2 - 5: Last Tango in Halifax: Season 3 The Midnight Swim (2014)
